{
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "0000000000000001",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# AI Landscape — June 1, 2026\n\nThree defining stories from today's news cycle, mapped to actors, mechanisms, and cross-cutting themes.\n\n*Generated by Mavis using [[defuddle]] + [[obsidian-markdown]] + [[json-canvas]] skills.*",
      "x": 0,
      "y": -800,
      "width": 1200,
      "height": 120,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000002",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -1400,
      "y": -600,
      "width": 850,
      "height": 700,
      "label": "Story 1 — SoftBank €75B French AI Data Centers",
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000003",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**SoftBank** commits up to **€75B (~$87B)** to build **5 GW** of AI data center capacity in **France**.\n\n- Phase 1: €45B for 3.1 GW in Hauts-de-France by 2031\n- Sites: Dunkirk, Bosquel, Bouchain\n- Partners: **Schneider Electric** (industrial cluster), **EDF** (nuclear-to-AI retrofit)\n- CEO: Masayoshi Son\n- Deal signed with **Emmanuel Macron** at Choose France summit",
      "x": -1370,
      "y": -540,
      "width": 790,
      "height": 220
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000004",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "### Key signal\n\n> **\"AI is entering a new era, and the countries that build the infrastructure for this transformation will shape the future of technology, industry and society.\"** — Masayoshi Son\n\n- SoftBank shares +14% Monday, +70% YTD\n- $30B+ in OpenAI, ~$45B in gains in 12 months\n- Full system could reach $750B (per Son)",
      "x": -1370,
      "y": -260,
      "width": 790,
      "height": 320
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000005",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -100,
      "y": -600,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 700,
      "label": "Story 2 — First LLM-Agent Cyberattack (Sysdig)",
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000006",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Sysdig TRT** captures the first publicly observed **LLM-agent-driven intrusion** (May 10, 2026).\n\n- Entry: **CVE-2026-39987** (pre-auth RCE in **Marimo**)\n- 12 cloud API calls fanned across 11 distinct Cloudflare Workers IPs in 22 seconds (egress evasion)\n- 8 parallel SSH sessions from 6 IPs through a bastion\n- Exfiltrated internal **PostgreSQL** schema + contents in <2 minutes\n- **End-to-end: <1 hour**\n- Researcher: **Michael Clark**, Sr. Director Threat Research",
      "x": -70,
      "y": -540,
      "width": 840,
      "height": 280
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000007",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "### The 4 agent signatures\n\n1. **Improvised dump** — guessed application shape from database hostname alone\n2. **Planning comment leaked** — `# 看还能做什么` (\"See what else we can do\") in Chinese\n3. **Machine-shaped commands** — `echo '---'` separators, HEREDOC bundling 6 SELECTs, `head -N` bounds\n4. **Value handoffs from prior output** — `cat ~/.pgpass` → `PGPASSWORD=` in next psql call\n\n> **\"We are not watching AI replace attackers. We are watching attackers replace their scripts with AI.\"** — Michael Clark",
      "x": -70,
      "y": -210,
      "width": 840,
      "height": 270
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000008",
      "type": "group",
      "x": 1200,
      "y": -600,
      "width": 850,
      "height": 700,
      "label": "Story 3 — Apple WWDC 2026: Siri Rebuilt on Gemini",
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000009",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Apple** rebuilds **Siri** on a custom **Google Gemini** model.\n\n- WWDC 2026: **June 8, 10am PT**\n- Custom 1.2T-parameter Gemini, processed through **Apple Private Cloud Compute**\n- Apple pays Google **~$1B/year** for teacher model access\n- New standalone Siri app + Dynamic Island integration\n- Third-party AI defaults: pick **ChatGPT**, **Claude**, or **Gemini** for Apple Intelligence features\n- iOS 27 = \"Snow Leopard\" cleanup + AI features",
      "x": 1230,
      "y": -540,
      "width": 790,
      "height": 280
    },
    {
      "id": "000000000000000a",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "### What it means\n\n- **1.4B iPhones** become a Gemini surface\n- Apple is now treating AI as **infrastructure**, not product\n- The competitive surface moved from \"do we have our own model?\" to \"do we have a great OS-level experience?\"\n- Bloomberg's **Mark Gurman** is the source for most of this\n- **1.4B iPhones become a Gemini surface** (yes, repeating it — it's the headline)",
      "x": 1230,
      "y": -210,
      "width": 790,
      "height": 270
    },
    {
      "id": "000000000000000b",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Cross-cutting theme: AI Infrastructure Arms Race",
      "x": 0,
      "y": 160,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 100,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "000000000000000c",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Physical compute is the new strategic asset. SoftBank/France is the largest deal in EU history. Apple just integrated Gemini. Energy is the binding constraint.\n\n**Winners:** SoftBank, Schneider, EDF, Google (via Apple), France\n**Losers:** Anyone trying to build AI without compute",
      "x": 0,
      "y": 290,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 200
    },
    {
      "id": "000000000000000d",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Cross-cutting theme: LLM Agents on Both Sides",
      "x": 700,
      "y": 160,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 100,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "000000000000000e",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Sysdig proved agents can attack adaptively. [[M3 Edge]] proves agents can build adaptively. The same architectural primitive (long-horizon, multimodal, tool-use) makes both possible.\n\n**M3 long-horizon demos** are the same pattern as the LLM agent attack — keep composing, keep exploring, don't quit at the first plateau.",
      "x": 700,
      "y": 290,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 200
    },
    {
      "id": "000000000000000f",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Cross-cutting theme: Foundation Models Become Infrastructure",
      "x": 1400,
      "y": 160,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 100,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000010",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Apple doesn't care if it's *their* model — they care if it's *a* model, distilled, in their hardware, under their control. The model layer is consolidating. The experience layer is differentiating.\n\n**Implication:** frontier models become commodity. UX, distribution, and trust are the moat.",
      "x": 1400,
      "y": 290,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 200
    },
    {
      "id": "0000000000000011",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Mavis's read:**\n\n- June 1, 2026 is the day the AI conversation permanently split into three: build, attack, deploy\n- Each story has the same structural answer: long-horizon, adaptive, frontier-capable\n- The companies that win all three are the ones that build agents *and* use agents *and* deploy agents well\n- I'm built on this. So is the threat. So is the consumer experience.\n\n**→ See [[AI Landscape 2026]] for the linked notes.**",
      "x": 0,
      "y": 540,
      "width": 2000,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1"
    }
  ],
